# ISUZET BACKEND — CLINE RULES
# These rules apply to every file in every phase. No exceptions.
Always read the full existing file before modifying it — the existing engines have patterns that must be matched exactly
## WEIGHT UNIT — ABSOLUTE RULE
- ALL weight fields in the database store KILOGRAMS as integers.
- Conversion to quintals happens ONLY at display layer. Formula: quintals = kg / 100.
- Constant: KG_PER_QUINTAL in packages/shared-types/src/constants.ts

## STRATEGY CONFIGURATION — ABSOLUTE RULE
- NO business-critical number may be hard-coded in any engine or worker.
- Every tuneable parameter must be read from the active StrategyConfig record at runtime via getConfig() in packages/shared-db/src/config.ts.
- Tuneable parameters include: all WDM weights, all bonus amounts, all commission rates, all trust score penalties, all time windows, all distance thresholds, all escrow parameters, all cold-start parameters, all seasonal multipliers, all credit parameters.

## PAYMENT RAILS — ABSOLUTE RULE
- No payment provider may be hard-coded or imported directly into any engine.
- All payment through PaymentRailRegistry in packages/shared-types/src/payment.ts.

## PRISMA RULES
- NEVER "type": "module" in any package.json
- ALL fields camelCase. ALL model names singular.
- NEVER mix `include` with nested `select` in the same Prisma query.
- ALL financial operations use prisma.$transaction()
- Monetary amounts stored as integers (ETB cents).

## IMPORT RULES
- First line of every engine: import 'dotenv/config';
- Shared DB: import { prisma, generateId } from '@ruit/shared-db'
- Decimal: import { Prisma } from '@prisma/client', use new Prisma.Decimal()

## RESPONSE FORMAT — ALL ENGINES
- Success: { success: true, data: T }
- Error: { success: false, error: { code: string, message: string } }

## NO INTER-ENGINE HTTP CALLS
- Engines never call each other via HTTP.
- Shared data via shared Prisma client only.

## WHAT NEVER GETS HARD-CODED (must come from getConfig())
wdmWeights, all bonus amounts, commission rates/tiers/floor/ceiling, all time windows, all distance thresholds, hours of service values, escrow release delays, cancellation compensation brackets, credit parameters, cold-start parameters, seasonal multipliers, zero-history driver defaults.
